# TrackFresh — normal Cursor workflow

## Project

- **Finish copy:** `/Users/frederickbigler/Documents/Projects/trackfresh-fresh` — work here until the app is done; **commit + push to `main`** is the final deploy step (do not commit until the user asks).
- **Remote:** `https://github.com/Frederickb1962/trackfresh.git`
- **Deploy:** push to `main` → Vercel → trackfresh.ai
- **Open workspace:** `trackfresh-fresh.code-workspace` (not the parent `Projects` folder) so dev server, preview URL, and layout restore apply.

## Layout (restore if broken)

- **Left:** File explorer (primary sidebar)
- **Center:** **Live app preview** (Simple Browser → `http://127.0.0.1:3000/?enter=1`)
- **Right:** Agents chat panel
- **Code:** open `app/page.js` in a second tab or split when editing

Preferred preview URL is saved in workspace settings as `trackfresh.preview.url`.

If layout is wrong after a Cursor update:

1. `workbench.sideBar.location` should be `"left"` (set in `.vscode/settings.json`)
2. Click the **gear icon** (top-right) → set **Agent Sidebar** to **Right**
3. Press **⌘E** to toggle Agent / Editor layout if needed
4. Open **`trackfresh-fresh.code-workspace`** (not an empty workspace) so layout restores reliably
5. If preview is missing: **⌘⇧P** → `Tasks: Run Task` → `TrackFresh: Restore Editing Layout` or `npm run preview`

## Dev server & preview

**Run these yourself** — never tell the user to use an external Mac terminal:

- `npm run dev` or `npm run dev:clean` — start dev server on :3000
- `npm run preview` — open Simple Browser in Cursor center (uses saved `trackfresh.preview.url`)
- On folder open, task **TrackFresh: Restore Editing Layout** auto-starts dev server + preview (allow automatic tasks when prompted)

Manual fallback: **⌘⇧P** → `Tasks: Run Task` → `TrackFresh: Restore Editing Layout`

Or: **Run and Debug** panel → `TrackFresh: Dev + Simple Browser`

## UX changes (user approval required)

- **Default:** copy/text only (headings, hints, translations, button labels).
- **Ask first** before changing layout, colors, spacing, grid/tile sizes, navigation order, or component structure.
- If the user says layouts changed without approval, revert the visual diff (e.g. `git show HEAD:app/page.js` for the Explore tiles block) and keep non-visual fixes (API bugs, copy).

## Git

- Run `git status`, `git diff`, `git add`, `git commit`, `git push` yourself
- Remote uses HTTPS; macOS Keychain stores credentials after first login
- When user says **commit and deploy**: status → diff → commit → push to `main`
